{"name":"Star Trek Adventures Compendia - Manual","pages":[{"sort":100000,"name":"Start","type":"text","_id":"iWVi8WH1MxKBxefE","title":{"show":false,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/sta-compendia-logo.png\" /><h1>Welcome to the future!</h1><p>The Unofficial <em>Star Trek Adventures Compendia</em> are designed to get your game set up fast and frictionless.</p><p>This module contains ready-made Talents, Items, Shipframes, and much more. Due to the permission granted by Modiphius Entertaiment Ltd. to adopt <em>Star Trek Adventures</em> the module is limited to \"player-facing\" content from the original Starfleet <em>Core Rulebook</em>.</p><p>Especially, the stats of NPC characters and starships are not included in the compendia. However, we have included icons, tokens, and templates to allow Gamemasters to quickly create missing assets using a copy of the <em>Core Rulebook</em> for personal use.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Feature Overview","type":"text","_id":"6FXnGgijkg0u1zei","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Star Trek Adventures Compendia provides digital representations of most player-facing content from the <em>Star Trek Adventures Core Rulebook</em> by Modiphius Entertainment. Due to the terms of the permission granted by Modiphius we cannot provide content that is meant to be used by Gamemasters only (e.g. NPC abilities and stats). We do however provide icons, weapons and templates for Gamemasters to rapidly create this content for personal use.</p><h1>Starships</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/ships/starfleet/galaxy-token.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><ul><li><p>3D-rendered tokens for all Starfleet and alien vessels (modules/sta-compendia/assets/ships)</p></li><li><p>Spaceframe templates for all Starfleet vessels (Actor &gt; Starfleet Starships)</p></li><li><p>Empty placeholders for alien starships, that can be used by Gamemasters to swiftly create the NPC starships (Actor &gt; Alien Starships)</p></li></ul><h1>Starship Damage</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/damage-core/damage-disabled-engines.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>Compendium of items to represent damage to starship systems (Item &gt; Damage)</p></li><li><p>A Rollable Table to determine which system is hit when a ship takes damage @UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.veM6BxRbs9N8kzpV]{System Hit}</p></li><li><p>Icons for all systems and damage states (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/damage-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Talents</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/talents-core/talent-peace.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><p>Talents are separated into four compendia:</p><ul><li><p>Item &gt; Species Talents: Personal talents granted by character species</p></li><li><p>Item &gt; General Talents: Personal talents not belonging to any specific discipline</p></li><li><p>Item &gt; Discipline Talents: Personal talents that are strongly related to one of the six disciplines</p></li><li><p>Item &gt; Starship Talents: Talents for use with a Starship</p></li><li><p>50+ Icons for illustrating Talents (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/talents-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Focuses</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/focuses-core/focus-academy.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>A collection of 100+ example focuses mentioned in the player-facing part of the \"Core Rulebook\" (Item &gt; Focuses)</p></li><li><p>50+ Icons for illustrating focuses (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/focuses-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Values</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/values-core/value-vulcan.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>A collection of 50+ example values mentioned in the player-facing part of the \"Core Rulebook\" (Item &gt; Values)</p></li><li><p>50+ Icons for illustrating values (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/values-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Personal Equipment</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/items-core/tricorder.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><ul><li><p>Tools and Gear for personal use (Item &gt; Personal Equipment)</p></li><li><p>10+ Icons for illustrating personal equipment (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/items-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Personal Weapons</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/weapons-core/phaser-type-3-phaser-rifle.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><ul><li><p>Blade and fire weapons as well as hand-to-hand techniques (Item &gt; Personal Weapons)</p></li><li><p>10+ Icons for illustrating personal weapons (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/weapons-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Roles</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/roles-core/role-chief-medical-officer.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>Roles for starship crews modelled as talents (Item &gt; Roles)</p></li><li><p>10 Icons to uniquely illustrate each role (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/roles-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Starship Weapons</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/starshipweapons-core/weapon-phaser-bank.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>Ready-made weapons to equip on starships (Items &gt; Starship Weapons)</p></li><li><p>20+ icons for illustrating starship weapons (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/starship-weapons-core)</p></li></ul><h1>NPC and Starship Tokens</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/tokens-core/faction-romulan-rank-5-token.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>250+ generic icons for non-player characters and ships (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/tokens-core)</p></li></ul><h1>Lifepath creation</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/plain-core/plain-bajoran.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>Rollable Tables for all steps of the lifepath creation process that can be randomized</p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.C7ZWAeT9YjdRipNj]{Lifepath 1: Random Species (Enterprise)}, @UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.ijPLC6rwjpQ6W8xq]{Lifepath 1: Random Species (The Original Series)}, or @UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.yY8uHyDxEfOHGeGz]{Lifepath 1: Random Species (The Next Generation)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.aKVBsqSbuYnmFeEB]{Lifepath 2: Environment}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.NueUPiMP70nWmi1Z]{Lifepath 3: Upbringing}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.JIbzWYcHz5otzZcT]{Lifepath 4: Starfleet Academy}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.roll-tables-core.qMEWfy06mgKiNdm4]{Lifepath 6: Career Events}</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Journal Entries for each of the eight playable species. (Journal Entry &gt; Playable Species)</p></li></ul><h1>Additional Assets</h1><img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/plain-core/plain-custom.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><ul><li><p>50+ borderless general purpose icons for illustration (modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/plain-core)</p></li><li><p>A Battlemap with an empty Sector of Space</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":300000,"name":"Tutorials","type":"text","_id":"DQW2rg1BTt1oLblf","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/plain-core/plain-academy.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><p>This section of the manual describes how to best utilize the Compendia.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"Setting Up A New World","type":"text","_id":"PzNot7Bat6bFKpMw","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/plain-core/plain-heritage.svg\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /><p>This is the recommended setup for a new world for playing \"Star Trek Adventures\":</p><h1>Recommended Modules</h1><p>To maximize the potential of Foundry VTT for use with the \"Star Trek Adventures (Unofficial)\" game system, the following modules are strongly recommended:</p><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://foundryvtt.com/packages/sta-lcars-ui\">LCARS UI for Star Trek Adventures (Unofficial)</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://foundryvtt.com/packages/sta-initiative\">Star Trek Adventures Initiative</a></p></li></ul><h1>A Word on Importing Assets from Compendia</h1><p>Limit imports from the compendia into your game world to an absolute minimum. This is important. The reason is two-fold:</p><ul><li><p>Text and item stats of content that is imported into your game world become cloned copies separate from their compendia and this module. Hence, they will not receive updates and corrections when the module does.</p></li><li><p>Also, copies of compendium content increase the load time of your world for you and all players.</p></li></ul>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":400000,"name":"Creating a Player Starship","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/ships/starfleet/miranda-token.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><p>This is the recommended procedure for creating a player starship with the compendia:</p><ol><li><p>Open the compendium <em>Actor &gt; Starfleet Starships</em></p></li><li><p>Import the correct spaceframe template (either right-click &gt; Import, or drag-and-drop)</p></li><li><p>Find the template in the Actors panel and open its sheet</p></li><li><p>Rename the ship, decide on service date, mission profile (page 251 of the <em>Core Rulebook</em>), and corresponding talent</p></li><li><p>Apply Department modifiers from the mission profile</p></li><li><p>Open the Starship Talent compendium <em>Item &gt; Starship Talents</em> and drag-and-drop the chosen talent onto the sheet</p></li><li><p>Handle refits and change System scores accordingly (page 252 of the <em>Core Rulebook</em>)</p></li><li><p>If the ship has fewer talents than its scale indicates, pick additional talents and drag-and-drop them from the Starship Talent compendium <em>Item &gt; Starship Talents</em></p></li><li><p>Check if Resistance has been modified by any talents and update it accordingly</p></li><li><p>Set Shields and Power to maximum</p></li><li><p>Close the Sheet and in the Actor panel right-click to configure ownership</p></li></ol><blockquote><p>Note: All Starfleet spaceframe templates have prototype tokens that link back to the actor data. I.e. each token and the entry in the Actor panel open the same instance of the Sheet. This makes sense for a player starship that is unique and persistent across maps.</p><p>However, if you want to create template for multiple NPC ships of a class (think the fleet from \"The Ultimate Computer\"), you may want to edit the Prototype Token and uncheck <em>Link Actor Data</em>. Then each token references its own copy of the Sheet, and changes to one Sheet are not synced to any other version of that ship.</p></blockquote>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"mzdumRpvWsM3SitT"},{"sort":400000,"name":"Ready NPC Starships","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/ships/klingon/b-rel-token.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><p>Due to the terms granted by Modiphius Ltd. we do not provide stats for NPC Starships. However, we provide templates, to add them yourself. As a gamemaster, you can easily complete them so you have them handy for your group's adventures.</p><ol><li><p>Duplicate the compendium <em>Actors &gt; Alien Starships</em> and give it an easily identifiable name like <em>Ready NPC Starships.</em></p></li><li><p>Now open this compendium and use it exclusively for the following steps. It is tied to your current world. Only edit the starships you are likely to use, or be prepared to move your compendium to a new module. <strong>Don't unlock and edit the compendium of the </strong><em><strong>sta-compendium</strong></em><strong> module. It will be reset by each version update.</strong></p></li><li><p>Open a ship you would like to flesh out from the open compendum list. Don't import it just yet.</p><ol><li><p>For each ship you will find the relevant page of the <em>Core Rulebook</em> in the <em>Notes</em> section of the Sheet. Copy the traits, systems and department values, scale and resistance from the book.</p></li><li><p>Add attacks. All weapons that are described in the section <em>Starship Weaponry</em> (page 253 of the <em>Core Rulebook</em>) are available pre-made in the compendium <em>Item &gt; Starship Weapons</em> and can be simply dragged-and-dropped to the sheet. Copy additional weapons from the <em>Core Rulebook</em>. There are 20+ icons for illustration purposes available under <em>modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/starshipweapons-core</em>.</p></li><li><p>Add special rules (as talents). If special rules are also available as talents for players, you can simply drag and drop them from the compendium <em>Item &gt; Starship Talents</em>. Copy additional special rules from the <em>Core Rulebook</em>. There are 50+ icons for illustration purposes available under <em>modules/sta-compendia/assets/icons/talents-core</em>.</p></li><li><p>Optionally, add the crew quality. We provide each quality modeled as a talent, than you can drag-and-drop from the <em>Item &gt; Starship Talents</em> compendium.</p></li><li><p>Optionally, replace the text in the <em>Notes</em> section with the description from the <em>Core Rulebook</em>.</p></li><li><p>Set shields and power to maximum.</p></li></ol></li></ol>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"Vwj8PwK2tXpggJXb"},{"sort":400000,"name":"Creating an NPC Starship","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<img src=\"modules/sta-compendia/assets/ships/dominion/jem-hadar-battle-cruiser-token.webp\" style=\"display:block;margin:0px auto\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /><p>This is the recommended procedure for creating an alien non-player starship with the compendia:</p><ol><li><p>Open the compendium you created using the Tutorial @UUID[Compendium.sta-compendia.manual-tutorials-core.w6U4HlhU66tSmYhP.JournalEntryPage.Vwj8PwK2tXpggJXb]{Populating NPC Starships}</p></li><li><p>If it is a generic ship only used on one map, simply drag-and drop-the ship from the compendium to the map (then you are done, otherwise continue below)</p></li><li><p>If the ship is recurring and/or used on multiple maps, import it as an actor</p></li><li><p>Open the imported ship's sheet and customize its name and/or other values as needed</p></li><li><p>Open the prototype token, change the name and check <em>Link Actor Data</em></p></li><li><p>Add the ship to any map by dragging-and-dropping it from the <em>Actors</em> side-bar panel</p></li></ol><blockquote><p>You can also create NPC ships by using the templates found under <em>Actor &gt; Starfleet Starships</em>.</p><p>Note that these must still be modified using a mission profile (page 251 of the <em>Core Rulebook</em>) and thus should always be imported and customized before use. Also, the Prototype Tokens of these templates always have <em>Link Actor Data</em> enabled. Make sure to uncheck the option if you are planning on using the template for a fleet of generic ships.</p></blockquote>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_id":"N4tjMNbHEULIzT1N"}],"ownership":{"default":0,"b3MVB0kAwuP1VMcv":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.3xxmZ9Ef4F9FUhsL"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"sta","systemVersion":"1.1.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1666103310839,"modifiedTime":1676976385358,"lastModifiedBy":"b3MVB0kAwuP1VMcv"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"w6U4HlhU66tSmYhP"}
